{"name":"Answer chat messages in real time for Lead Bots","nodes":[{"parameters":{"public":true,"options":{}},"type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chatTrigger","typeVersion":1.1,"position":[-270,400],"id":"07141aca-84eb-4213-afac-59a0292c8760","name":"When Chat Message Received","webhookId":"896959e8-da6b-42b3-8893-d2daba632f34"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"0d8e4c7a-6531-48a3-9d82-9ffdf0a45599","name":"sessionId","value":"={{ $json.sessionId || $json.id || $execution.id }}","type":"string"},{"id":"b6d3c94d-150e-495b-b089-0cbef49ef707","name":"receivedAt","value":"={{ $now.toISO() }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[54,400],"id":"0a8b084b-9e57-4223-9c68-6026569cd004","name":"Stamp & Shape Conversation"},{"parameters":{"conditions":{"options":{"caseSensitive":true,"leftValue":"","typeValidation":"strict","version":2},"conditions":[{"id":"93aac4fb-5ab9-438d-a90e-34797cc27672","leftValue":"={{ $json.sessionId }}","rightValue":"","operator":{"type":"string","operation":"notEmpty"}}],"combinator":"and"}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.if","typeVersion":2.2,"position":[378,400],"id":"64b0cb2d-ad49-4da8-82fa-f2a4d9c63285","name":"Payload Valid?"},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Conversation Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[378,910],"id":"ac9e164c-fd76-48a1-aed2-59eccef631d6","name":"Record Rejected Input","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"promptType":"define","text":"={{ $json.chatInput || $json.message || JSON.stringify($json) }}","options":{"systemMessage":"You are a lead bots specialist for the chatbots & conversational ai team. Use the attached tools to look up real data before answering — never invent conversation details. Keep answers under 150 words, cite which tool you used, and escalate anything you cannot verify.","maxIterations":8}},"type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent","typeVersion":2.2,"position":[702,400],"id":"78bcb891-8df0-4430-a1db-e3686da4e069","name":"Reason & Act (AI Agent)","onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"model":"models/gemini-2.5-flash","options":{}},"type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatGoogleGemini","typeVersion":1,"position":[945,970],"id":"e9a1e637-38d9-4f0e-af13-69b470043dba","name":"Google Gemini Chat Model"},{"parameters":{},"type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.toolWikipedia","typeVersion":1,"position":[945,1390],"id":"c292ab17-5290-475f-be70-350ddf45f633","name":"Search Reference Wiki"},{"parameters":{},"type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.toolThink","typeVersion":1,"position":[1174,1390],"id":"3b8754db-8a2e-4312-b31c-ace7682c71e2","name":"Think It Through"},{"parameters":{"name":"score_helper","description":"Compute a quality score for a conversation record.","jsCode":"const j = JSON.parse(query);\nreturn String((j.signals || []).length * 10);"},"type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.toolCode","typeVersion":1.3,"position":[1633,1390],"id":"be0ac182-e1a4-419c-b072-e8f4e32142a0","name":"Custom Logic Tool"},{"parameters":{},"type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.toolCalculator","typeVersion":1,"position":[2322,1390],"id":"f68c1602-f3c8-4828-a0cb-cbf0dfccffd5","name":"Run Calculations"},{"parameters":{"sessionIdType":"customKey","sessionKey":"={{ $json.sessionId || $execution.id }}","contextWindowLength":12},"type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.memoryBufferWindow","typeVersion":1.3,"position":[2079,970],"id":"1f1f30a4-c7f8-4496-8676-451b6aa279a9","name":"Conversation Memory"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"ea48a100-a876-4384-8e67-be7c3327dc7d","name":"answer","value":"={{ $json.output }}","type":"string"},{"id":"d65859d3-ba0d-4fec-a5cc-807a0b30fa11","name":"confidence","value":"={{ $json.output && $json.output.length > 40 ? 'high' : 'low' }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[2646,400],"id":"aed1c719-5f23-4229-b1fa-6a9ab6eb9e28","name":"Shape Agent Output"},{"parameters":{"conditions":{"options":{"caseSensitive":true,"leftValue":"","typeValidation":"strict","version":2},"conditions":[{"id":"7ff952f4-ae27-4987-affb-08d42651a88c","leftValue":"={{ $json.confidence }}","rightValue":"high","operator":{"type":"string","operation":"equals"}}],"combinator":"and"}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.if","typeVersion":2.2,"position":[2970,400],"id":"524180df-f1b1-478d-941c-407909e7a61b","name":"Confident Enough?"},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Conversation Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[3294,160],"id":"5bbc57e9-4d15-44df-8222-5839c16f01e1","name":"Deliver Answer + Log to Google Sheets","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#support","cachedResultName":"#support"},"text":"=🙋 Low-confidence answer needs review: {{ $json.answer }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[3618,760],"id":"8cacf0aa-67f8-4b38-b7d9-a9ce59452978","name":"Escalate to Human Queue","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"mode":"append","numberInputs":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.merge","typeVersion":3.2,"position":[4266,400],"id":"30a228c0-7e9c-4bc0-920b-2f6a9658b31e","name":"Join Outcomes"},{"parameters":{"operation":"getCurrentDate","outputFieldName":"completedAt","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.dateTime","typeVersion":2,"position":[5238,400],"id":"45c53926-d865-4625-9d09-689fe9bed447","name":"Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"dataToSave":{"values":[{"key":"runId","value":"={{ $execution.id }}"},{"key":"itemCount","value":"={{ $items().length }}"}]}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.executionData","typeVersion":1,"position":[5562,400],"id":"4d5b9f9b-297a-4e69-9292-9c6843929430","name":"Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"aa23789c-40af-48fa-b64e-416d03ba19a7","name":"runAt","value":"={{ $now.toISO() }}","type":"string"},{"id":"6d7f44fc-6903-43e5-afe3-5114f4e3aaa8","name":"itemCount","value":"={{ $input.all().length }}","type":"number"},{"id":"bbdf3c1c-a3f1-47a6-bb5a-faf3657a191d","name":"status","value":"completed","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[5886,400],"id":"4105ce13-3d14-499c-aae1-d7b13fb0701a","name":"Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Conversation Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[6210,400],"id":"3c1dd16d-8be7-4df6-a982-ec31166406cf","name":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#support","cachedResultName":"#support"},"text":"=✅ Answer chat messages in real time for Lead Bots — run completed at {{ $now.toFormat('HH:mm') }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[6534,400],"id":"60c81e9a-cab7-4b5b-b7e7-3274e7f8b67d","name":"Send Summary to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"9d0e0d50-d360-4423-b0e1-54121e506b56","name":"failedNode","value":"={{ $json.error?.node?.name || 'unknown' }}","type":"string"},{"id":"94915ca0-d560-493b-a498-13bdb3ec7dfb","name":"errorMessage","value":"={{ $json.error?.message || JSON.stringify($json).slice(0,200) }}","type":"string"},{"id":"aeda4e32-bed1-49f4-b1e8-86f6230f3c7a","name":"workflow","value":"={{ $workflow.name }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[5886,1420],"id":"1b9d98bf-7a15-4d5b-a497-8d417696eb61","name":"Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#support","cachedResultName":"#support"},"text":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[6210,1420],"id":"44fed1b7-2526-4e64-9b70-804fa7bfd9b8","name":"Escalate Failure to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Conversation Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[6534,1420],"id":"212352ef-2e79-4367-a876-9e00fa6b9384","name":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### When Chat Message Received\n\nOpens a hosted chat session; every user message starts an execution with `chatInput` + `sessionId`.\n\nNext: Stamp & Shape Conversation","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"f8045b05-cdfe-730b-168c-3f0e2a1addf8","name":"Note: When Chat Message Received"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp & Shape Conversation\n\nShapes the item: writes `sessionId`, `receivedAt`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Payload Valid?","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"660f0f03-7a81-068e-bace-ee850b5bc9e3","name":"Note: Stamp & Shape Conversation"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Payload Valid?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.sessionId }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reason & Act (AI Agent) · ②→ Record Rejected Input","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"c7f3a914-212a-26a7-0f0c-be257a5d93c8","name":"Note: Payload Valid?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Rejected Input\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,1030],"id":"226cd5a0-fcde-5017-e3a8-03af9d455dc3","name":"Note: Record Rejected Input"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Reason & Act (AI Agent)\n\nThe AI brain: reads the input, decides which attached tools to call (and in what order), then composes the answer.\n\nPorts: ①→ Shape Agent Output · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"13dcd777-d5e3-670a-05f0-6e116e621b3d","name":"Note: Reason & Act (AI Agent)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Google Gemini Chat Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `models/gemini-2.5-flash`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Reason & Act (AI Agent)** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 Google AI API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[885,1090],"id":"8288f798-81ab-ddb1-00f5-5f66cd3da060","name":"Note: Google Gemini Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Search Reference Wiki\n\nReference lookup tool for general-knowledge questions.\n\nFeeds **Reason & Act (AI Agent)** as `tool`","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[885,1510],"id":"0cf16f1c-d9b7-a268-1047-efd24e0be7f2","name":"Note: Search Reference Wiki"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Think It Through\n\nScratchpad tool: lets the agent reason step-by-step before acting.\n\nFeeds **Reason & Act (AI Agent)** as `tool`","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1114,1750],"id":"79f36e9d-24e0-a6a5-253d-a903d9753ce6","name":"Note: Think It Through"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Custom Logic Tool\n\nDeterministic code helper the agent can invoke for exact computation.\n\nFeeds **Reason & Act (AI Agent)** as `tool`","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1573,1510],"id":"a1828718-7269-38b1-bd84-ad290c71cedb","name":"Note: Custom Logic Tool"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Run Calculations\n\nMath tool — keeps arithmetic exact instead of letting the LLM guess.\n\nFeeds **Reason & Act (AI Agent)** as `tool`","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2262,1510],"id":"fe15bcb9-3134-d8df-829d-903839e12632","name":"Note: Run Calculations"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Conversation Memory\n\nConversation memory keyed by session — the bot remembers earlier turns for each user separately.\n\nFeeds **Reason & Act (AI Agent)** as `memory`","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2019,1090],"id":"3d45e7a2-29ef-23df-2e91-51def6e79386","name":"Note: Conversation Memory"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Shape Agent Output\n\nShapes the item: writes `answer`, `confidence`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Confident Enough?","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2586,520],"id":"e0504205-7a35-b845-6b14-cdd3c907b69a","name":"Note: Shape Agent Output"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Confident Enough?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.confidence }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Deliver Answer + Log to Google Sheets · ②→ Escalate to Human Queue","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2910,520],"id":"bbaf1921-50fe-3a29-83a2-619b29101923","name":"Note: Confident Enough?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Deliver Answer + Log to Google Sheets\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Join Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3234,280],"id":"b261a1a7-6ea3-1576-2ffe-f9c67e60201e","name":"Note: Deliver Answer + Log to Google Sheets"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate to Human Queue\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Join Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,880],"id":"ab279557-a207-b37a-6290-c095c596f133","name":"Note: Escalate to Human Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Join Outcomes\n\nRejoins 2 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4206,520],"id":"9c5be07b-5ef1-4cbd-d4f9-f9c2f3a64f71","name":"Note: Join Outcomes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"67ce767d-ef55-5838-de19-86daf27e3546","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"08b7f6d8-d453-9df3-fab4-244244e6ca4e","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,520],"id":"19a09373-b1da-0467-2610-7ec1a9576a52","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,520],"id":"34c75dc7-366d-3f73-6858-65116a0bebd0","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,520],"id":"ab947497-63c3-d02a-951e-9b2573f29bd1","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,1540],"id":"92f27fc1-9b17-2aaf-0a2b-53a3177b9b88","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,1540],"id":"34c02b02-6a6a-ae4c-3517-5011958d87a1","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,1540],"id":"fe34ab1c-ab18-6bb6-ee54-15f805f37866","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Answer chat messages in real time for Lead Bots\n\n**Pattern:** Chatbot Responder · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Chat\n\n## What it does\nAnswer chat messages in real time for Lead Bots. It responds live to chat messages.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual lead bots is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nWhen Chat Message Received → Stamp & Shape Conversation → Payload Valid? → Reason & Act (AI Agent) → Shape Agent Output → Confident Enough? → Deliver Answer + Log to Google Sheets → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to chatbot responder without manual effort\n- Anyone automating lead bots in customer support\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Responds in seconds\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google AI API key; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"e3910eb0-cf84-18bf-6196-5d90a358ff98","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-260],"id":"c4eec7fd-46d5-ea84-f25d-af102e985b91","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-260],"id":"7925bb6c-017f-f6a9-a47a-aa4d367c18a8","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your lead bots process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-260],"id":"f25eb53b-a3ab-bb55-f550-239905dff2f6","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"When Chat Message Received":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp & Shape Conversation","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp & Shape Conversat